        <bioghist id="ref4">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Bernhard J. Stern (1894-1956) was a social scientist and political radical who came under persecution from Congressional investigative committees during the McCarthy period. The materials in the collection were assembled by Samuel W. Bloom, a sociology professor who wrote an article on Stern, "The Intellectual in a Time of Crisis," for Volume 26 of the 
                <emph render="italic">Journal of the History of the Behavioral Sciences</emph>.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The documents pertain to Bloom's writing of the article and contains drafts of the article, correspondence related to it, and much of the documentation and research used in its writing. PLEASE DIRECT FURTHER INQUIRIES TO: peter.filardo@nyu.edu</p>
